{"type":"message","id":"31e04bff","parentId":"bbb5b569","timestamp":"2026-04-22T04:50:12.743Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_x0nzavw13fet_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Driving Training Management System - Backend\n\nThis is the robust, high-performance Node.js backend infrastructure running the Driving Training Management System API.\n\n---\n\n## 🏗 Architecture & Design\n\nThe backend strictly conforms to **Clean Architecture** patterns, ensuring a resilient separation of concerns.\n\n- **`domain/`**: Enterprise logic, business rules, models, and robust abstractions. Independent of any frameworks.\n- **`application/`**: Use cases and application-specific logic (`services/`).\n- **`interface/`**: Presentation layer handling HTTP connections (`controllers/`, `routes/`, `middlewares/`).\n- **`infrastructure/`**: Database implementations (`repositories/`), caching, sockets, and heavy integrations.\n\n---\n\n## 🛠 Technology Stack\n\n- **Runtime**: [Node.js 20+](https://nodejs.org/)\n- **Framework**: [Express.js](https://expressjs.com/)\n- **Language**: TypeScript (Strict Typing enforced)\n- **Database**: [MongoDB](https://www.mongodb.com/) via [Mongoose](https://mongoosejs.com/)\n- **State/Caching**: Node `node-cache`\n- **Real-time Engine**: [Socket.io](https://socket.io/)\n- **Validation**: [Joi](https://joi.dev/)\n- **Logging**: [Winston](https://github.com/winstonjs/winston) (Mandatory system wide logs, NO `console.log`)\n- **Package Manager**: [Yarn](https://yarnpkg.com/)\n\n---\n\n## 📁 Directory Layout\n\n```text\nbackend/\n├── src/\n│   ├── application/       # Service layer (Student, Auth, Payment)\n│   ├── domain/            # Entities and domain exceptions\n│   ├── infrastructure/    # Mongoose Models, DB Connections, WebSockets\n│   ├── interface/         # Express Controllers, Routes, and request Middlewares\n│   └── index.ts           # Application entry point/Bootstrapper\n├── tests/                 # Unit & End-to-End tests\n├── .env.example           # Example Secrets\n├── eslint.config.cjs      # ESLint strict guidelines\n└── tsconfig.json          # TypeScript definitions\n```\n\n---\n\n## ⚙️ Configuration & Execution\n\n### Requirements\n- Node.js >= 20.x\n- Yarn >= 1.22.x\n- MongoDB (Local instance or Atlas cluster)\n\n### 1. Install Dependencies\nYou **MUST** use `yarn` for installation to avoid lockfile conflicts.\n\n```bash\ncd backend\nyarn install\n```\n\n### 2. Environment Variables\n\nCopy `.env.example` to `.env` and fill the variables:\n\n```env\nPORT=5000\nMONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/ahv-system\nJWT_SECRET=super_secret_string\nJWT_EXPIRES_IN=24h\nNODE_ENV=development\n```\n\n### 3. Run the Server\n\n```bash\n# Start in development mode (nodemon + ts-node)\nyarn dev\n\n# Compile safely for production environments\nyarn build\n\n# Run production compiled application\nyarn start\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🛡️ Coding Standards (Strict Workflow)\n\n1. **Never use `console.log`**. Instead, import your logger instance and utilise `logger.info()`, `logger.error()`, etc.\n2. **Never wrap controllers in manual `try/catch`**. All controllers must be wrapped using the `catchAsync` architectural middleware.\n3. **Consistent Error Envelope**. The system returns strict `{ success: boolean, data/message: any }` schemas.\n4. **No Static Methods**. Classes must use instance methods (no `static` methods).\n\n---\n\n## 🧪 Testing\n\n```bash\n# Run linting\nyarn lint\n\n# Execute Unit Tests\nyarn test\n```\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776833412724}}
